                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report of the Deputies</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Council examined a list prepared by the Deputies of outstanding questions in
                    connection with the Draft Treaty with Italy (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 140).<note n="18" xml:id="d203fn18">See footnote 13,
                            <ref target="#pg_617">p. 617</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard the report presented by the Chairman of the Deputies.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi> (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177).<note n="19" xml:id="d203fn19">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">United Nations’ Property in Italy. Compensation</hi>.
                    Appendix III, Part II, 2.<note n="20" xml:id="d203fn20">Appendix III of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177 is printed separately as
                            <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 133, June 5, 1946,
                            <ref target="#pg_463">p. 463</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>No agreement was reached on this matter.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Italian Property on Allied and Associated Powers’
                        Territory</hi> (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss>177).
                    Article 71.<note n="21" xml:id="d203fn21">Article 71 is quoted in full in
                        footnote 26, <ref target="#pg_517">p. 517</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S. Delegation proposed the following amendment to its original draft of
                    Article 71: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>in para. 1, the phrase “within the limits of its war claims against
                            Italy” to be replaced by the phrase “within the limits of its claims or
                            those of its nationals against Italy or its nationals.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0650" n="628" xml:id="pg_628"/>
                <p>An agreement in principle was reached on the U.S. proposal as amended.</p>
                <p>The article was referred back to the Economic Committee for drafting.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">General Economic Relations. Expropriation</hi>. (Appendix
                    IV, Part II).<note n="22" xml:id="d203fn22">Appendix IV of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M. (D) (46)</gloss> 177 is printed separately as
                            <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 167, June 12, 1946,
                            <ref target="#pg_488">p. 488</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council agreed to delete the clause which formed the subject of Part II.</p>
                <p>4. <hi rend="italic">Personal Injuries</hi> (Article 66).</p>
                <p>The Council agreed to delete this article.</p>
                <p>5. <hi rend="italic">Dodecanese</hi> (Article 12).</p>
                <p>The Soviet Delegation stated that it would table a proposal on this subject.</p>
                <p>6. <hi rend="italic">Settlement of Disputes</hi>, (Appendix II, Part II, 2<note n="23" xml:id="d203fn23">Appendix II of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D)
                            (46)</gloss> 177 is printed separately as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 138, June 5, 1946, <ref target="#pg_470">p.
                            470</ref>.</note> and Appendix III, Part II, 3.)</p>
                <p>This question to be examined by the Deputies.</p>
                <p>7. <hi rend="italic">Franco-Italian Frontier. Rectification No. 4</hi>. (<hi rend="italic">Tenda and Briga</hi>) (Article 2.)</p>
                <p>The examination of this question was adjourned.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Future Work of the Council</hi>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Committee on Colonies to meet on Wednesday, 26th June, at 10
                        a.m.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Deputies to meet on Wednesday, 26th June, at 11:30 a.m. and prepare a
                        list of outstanding questions in connection with the Draft Peace Treaties
                        with Italy, Roumania, Bulgaria, Hungary and Finland.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>The Council to hold its next meeting on Wednesday, 26th June, at 4
                        p.m.</item>
                </list>
